’Щ@de5eacc997ffa760da84693e1a2ca1d9a63c55b68869c0ad0ca6f528a7248596ЪRTitle: title: filter
Path: Examples
Content:
Filter items of a list according to a condition.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> [1 2] | filter {|x| $x > 1}
в•ӯв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв•®
в”Ӯ 0 в”Ӯ 2 в”Ӯ
в•°в”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв•Ҝ


```
Filter rows of a table according to a condition.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> [{a: 1} {a: 2}] | filter {|x| $x.a > 1}
в•ӯв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв•®
в”Ӯ # в”Ӯ a в”Ӯ
в”ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Ө
в”Ӯ 0 в”Ӯ 2 в”Ӯ
в•°в”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв•Ҝ


```
Filter rows of a table according to a stored condition.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> let cond = {|x| $x.a > 1}; [{a: 1} {a: 2}] | filter $cond
в•ӯв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв•®
в”Ӯ # в”Ӯ a в”Ӯ
в”ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Ө
в”Ӯ 0 в”Ӯ 2 в”Ӯ
в•°в”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв•Ҝ


```
Filter items of a range according to a condition.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 9..13 | filter {|el| $el mod 2 != 0}
в•ӯв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв•®
в”Ӯ 0 в”Ӯ  9 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 1 в”Ӯ 11 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ 2 в”Ӯ 13 в”Ӯ
в•°в”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв•Ҝ


```
List all numbers above 3, using an existing closure condition.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> let a = {$in > 3}; [1, 2, 5, 6] | filter $a


```
’Щ@c66a9f3574e05de165af0377c8c280812f96d4596dad772ec66fb0f248761c60Щ©Title: title: filter
Path: Notes
Content:
This command works similar to 'where' but can only use a closure as a predicate.

The "row condition" syntax is not supported.
